{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"97369ef1-126f-4659-9a97-4e40723d721a","content":"There are no pipeline files in this repo, so here's the general migration guidance:\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 → Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test project\n\nIn your `.csproj`, add:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace the pipeline task\n\n**Before** (VSTest@3):\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After** (DotNetCoreCLI@2 with `dotnet test`):\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | `dotnet test` (test is an exe) |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Publishing | Auto-published | Needs explicit `PublishTestResults@2` and `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |\n\n> **Tip:** If you use Coverlet instead of the built-in collector, replace `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` with `--collect:\"XPlat Code Coverage\"` and the output will already be Cobertura XML.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f218b7cc-f01c-4d42-8e18-301c3d54f48d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No pipeline files in the repo. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge of migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines.","outputTokens":675,"requestId":"082A:19EA3A:81401A8:8F6955C:69EABECC"},"id":"8091ce26-b585-40b8-85d5-e80892f8371d","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:52:40.589Z","parentId":"7662abef-6f76-4655-880e-4f8b6027da43"}
